almost /ˈɔːlməʊst/

1. ADV You use almost to indicate that something is not completely the case but is nearly the case. 差不多; 几乎 

例： The couple had been dating for almost three years. 这对情侣谈恋爱差不多三年了。 

例： The effect is almost impossible to describe. 这影响几乎无法言表。 

例： He contracted Spanish flu, which almost killed him. 他传染上了西班牙型流感，那几乎要了他的命。

</div>

